Top Five Safety Tips for Women:


Plan Ahead: Before heading out, always have a plan in place. Familiarize yourself with your surroundings, stay aware of who and what is nearby, and inform someone outside your group about your whereabouts.

 Share Your Location: Use the emergency features on your smartphone to ping your location to trusted contacts in case of an emergency.

 Carry Self-Defense Tools: Choose self-defense tools like pepper spray, a safety whistle, or a mini flashlight that you feel comfortable carrying. These items can be easily accessible by clipping them to your purse or keychain.

 Set Boundaries: Trust your instincts and don't hesitate to create distance from anyone who makes you feel uncomfortable or unsafe. Your safety is the priority, so prioritize it over politeness.

 Empower Yourself: Take a self-defense class to equip yourself both physically and mentally to handle potentially dangerous situations
